---
import PageLayout from "@/layouts/Base.astro";

const meta = {
	title: "Database Migration Tool Evaluator",
	description:
		"Detailed overview of a bachelor project evaluating database migration tools across real-world datasets.",
};
---

<PageLayout meta={meta}>
	<section>
		<p class="mb-6">
			<a class="cactus-link" href="/">← Back to Home</a>
		</p>
		<h1 class="title mb-8">Database Migration Tool Evaluator</h1>
		<div class="prose prose-sm prose-cactus max-w-none">
			<p>
				This bachelor project evaluates how well different migration tools move relational MySQL data
				into PostgreSQL and MongoDB. The study is based on real application datasets and compares
				accuracy, schema fidelity, performance, and operational usability.
			</p>

			<h2>Scope of the Evaluation</h2>
			<ul>
				<li>3 migration tools: pgLoader, MRM, and Mongify.</li>
				<li>3 real-world source databases: WordPress, WooCommerce, and ERPNext.</li>
				<li>68 tables and 2,108 rows analyzed.</li>
				<li>40-criteria weighted scoring framework used for final comparison.</li>
			</ul>

			<h2>Key Findings</h2>
			<ul>
				<li>pgLoader achieved the highest overall score for MySQL to PostgreSQL migration.</li>
				<li>MRM delivered strong MySQL to MongoDB results with a GUI-driven workflow.</li>
				<li>Mongify showed strong document transformation but lower consistency on one dataset.</li>
			</ul>

			<h2>Technical Environment</h2>
			<ul>
				<li>Docker-based setup for MySQL, PostgreSQL, and MongoDB.</li>
				<li>Python scripts used for migration analysis and reporting.</li>
				<li>Mermaid ERDs used for schema visualization and documentation.</li>
			</ul>

			<p>
				<strong>Repository:</strong>
				<a
					class="cactus-link ms-2"
					href="https://github.com/NickytaS/nathalie-thesis-project"
					rel="noreferrer"
					target="_blank"
				>
					github.com/NickytaS/nathalie-thesis-project
				</a>
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>
</PageLayout>
